    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>121500</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.106</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Φίλων">Φίλων</name></persName>                   
                    <lb n="1a"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philôn <supplied reason="subaudible">fils de</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philon <supplied reason="subaudible">son of</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philon <supplied reason="subaudible">figlio di</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>This base is presumably a funerary one, although it was impossible to check its upper side.
               Most bases collected lately in the Museum come from tombs around the town of Cyrene.</p>
	       <p>Philon is one of the most common names in Cyrene; without his father's name, it is impossible to try to relate him to any already known person.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
